Over the last five years 634 trees have been planted by Trees for the Future on behalf of Garfield High School's yearbook staff!

Thank you to all of the parents and students whose yearbook purchases have helped with this achievement.
shared_text:
The Bureau - GHS Yearbook
August 10 at 9:29 PM ·

Over the last 5 years our publisher TreeRing has partnered with Trees for the Future to plant a tree for every yearbook sold at GHS. This year our cumulative total came in at 634 trees planted between 2015-2020!

Great job James A. Garfield Local Schools, and thank you to the parents and students who purchase yearbooks every year.

You can learn more about the great work Trees for the Future does by visiting trees.org.
